The prefixes in this group change the directional verbs\linebreak (\sectref{sec:3.8.4.4.5}) into transitive verbs with the meaning `bring' or `take'. 	extstyleStyleVernacularWordsItalic{p}
obreakdash- is a neutral prefix and by far the most common one \REF{ex:3:x221}, 	extstyleStyleVernacularWordsItalic{amap}
obreakdash- is used when something is brought out in the open, often with the meaning `bring forth'. Usually there is a clear goal, a person or a place, which may not be mentioned in the clause itself but occurs in an earlier one \REF{ex:3:x430}, or is understood from the context \REF{ex:3:x222}. If the goal is explicitly mentioned in the clause, the neutral prefix is used \REF{ex:3:x221}, \REF{ex:3:x223}. The prefix 	extstyleStyleVernacularWordsItalic{aap}
obreakdash- \REF{ex:3:x224} is very rare and I have been unable to establish whether it really differs from 	extstyleStyleVernacularWordsItalic{amap}
obreakdash- or whether it is just a matter of idiolectal use. ootnote{The bring
obreakdash-	extsc{pr}efixes may have been grammaticalized from a medial verb construction involving the verb aaw
obreakdash- `take'. It is easy to see how aawep ekap
obreakdash- `take (and) come' could have developed into aapekap
obreakdash- `bring' and possibly also into pekap-. Another possibility is that it is a result of a related process to that in Usan where the verb 	extstyleFootnoteBaseChar{ba} `take' has contracted into 	extstyleFootnoteBaseChar{b}
obreakdash-, which has combined with verbs of motion and been lexicalized with the meaning of bringing or taking ({Reesink 1987}:144--145). The 	extstyleFootnoteBaseChar{amap}
obreakdash-	extsc{pr}efix may have its origin in the expression 	extstyleFootnoteBaseChar{	extit{ama-	extsc{pa}}} `in the sun', which implies `in the open'. There is also a very slight possibility that the p
obreakdash-prefix might be an Austronesian loan, as p(V)
obreakdash- is a common causative or transitivizer prefix in Austronesian languages \citep[61]{Bugenhagen1995}. 	extstyleFootnoteBaseChar{But all of this is just conjecture at this point.}}
